caption: If you look at the slope of the Eshima Ohashi bridge in Japan from the right angle, the “betabumi-zaka” ramp of the bridge looks like it’s shooting straight up into the sky.Betabumi-zaka means “a pedal-to-the-metal slope” in Japanese. The renowned bridge connects Sakaiminato in Tottori Prefecture and Matsue in Shimane Prefecture.
